{#
/**
 * Interactive Safety Map Page Template
 * 
 * DESIGN REFERENCE:
 * - docs/product/design/02-wireframes.md (Lines 855-922)
 * - docs/product/design/01-sitemap-navigation.md (Lines 355-392)
 * 
 * IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS:
 * - Full-page interactive map with Leaflet
 * - Sidebar with search and filters
 * - H3 hexagon overlay with risk colors
 * - Crime detail panel
 * - Responsive: sidebar collapses on mobile
 * 
 * PERFORMANCE:
 * - Lazy load map tiles
 * - Limit hexagons to viewport
 * - Use marker clustering
 * - See docs/product/design/06-performance-strategy.md (Lines 525-585)
 * 
 * ACCESSIBILITY:
 * - Alternative data view for screen readers
 * - Keyboard navigation for map controls
 * - See docs/product/design/05-accessibility-checklist.md (Lines 411-440)
 */
#}

<div class="safety-map-page">
  {# Sidebar (30% width, collapsible on mobile) #}
  <aside class="map-sidebar" role="complementary" aria-label="Map controls and information">
    {# Search Location #}
    <div class="sidebar-search">
      <label for="location-search" class="sidebar-label">Search Location</label>
      <div class="search-input-group">
        <input 
          type="search" 
          id="location-search" 
          class="search-input"
          placeholder="Enter address or zip code..." 
          aria-label="Search for a location"
        />
        <button type="button" class="search-button" aria-label="Search">
          <span class="icon-search" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    {# Risk Summary Card #}
    <div class="risk-summary-card">
      <h2 class="card-title">Current Location</h2>
      <div class="risk-indicator" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <span class="risk-icon" style="color: {{ risk_color }}" aria-hidden="true">
          {{ risk_icon }}
        </span>
        <div class="risk-info">
          <p class="risk-level" style="color: {{ risk_color }}">
            {{ risk_level }}
          </p>
          <p class="risk-score">
            Z-Score: <strong>{{ z_score }}</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="risk-description">
            {{ risk_description }}
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    {# Filters #}
    <div class="filter-panel">
      <h3 class="panel-title">Filters</h3>
      
      <div class="filter-group">
        <label for="time-range" class="filter-label">Time Range</label>
        <select id="time-range" class="filter-select" aria-label="Filter by time range">
          <option value="24h">Last 24 Hours</option>
          <option value="7d" selected>Last 7 Days</option>
          <option value="30d">Last 30 Days</option>
          <option value="3m">Last 3 Months</option>
          <option value="1y">Last Year</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      
      <div class="filter-group">
        <label for="crime-type" class="filter-label">Crime Type</label>
        <select id="crime-type" class="filter-select" aria-label="Filter by crime type">
          <option value="all" selected>All Types</option>
          <option value="violent">Violent Crimes</option>
          <option value="property">Property Crimes</option>
          <option value="drug">Drug-Related</option>
          <option value="other">Other</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      
      <button type="button" class="filter-apply" aria-label="Apply filters">
        Apply Filters
      </button>
    </div>
    
    {# Crime Statistics #}
    <div class="crime-stats">
      <h3 class="panel-title">Crime Statistics</h3>
      <dl class="stats-list">
        <div class="stat-item">
          <dt class="stat-label">Total Crimes:</dt>
          <dd class="stat-value">{{ total_crimes }}</dd>
        </div>
        
        <div class="stat-item">
          <dt class="stat-label">This Week:</dt>
          <dd class="stat-value">{{ weekly_crimes }}</dd>
        </div>
        
        <div class="stat-item">
          <dt class="stat-label">Trend:</dt>
          <dd class="stat-value trend-{{ trend }}">
            <span class="trend-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              {% if trend == 'improving' %}↓{% elseif trend == 'declining' %}↑{% else %}→{% endif %}
            </span>
            {{ trend_text }}
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
    
    {# Recent Crimes List #}
    <div class="recent-crimes">
      <h3 class="panel-title">Recent Crimes</h3>
      <ul class="crimes-list">
        {% for crime in recent_crimes %}
          <li class="crime-item">
            <span class="crime-type-badge" data-type="{{ crime.type }}">
              {{ crime.type }}
            </span>
            <span class="crime-time">{{ crime.time_ago }}</span>
            <button 
              type="button" 
              class="crime-details-btn"
              aria-label="View details for {{ crime.type }} crime"
              data-crime-id="{{ crime.id }}"
            >
              Details
            </button>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </aside>
  
  {# Map Container (70% width) #}
  <main class="map-container" role="main" aria-label="Interactive crime map">
    <div id="crime-map" class="crime-map" role="application" aria-label="Crime map showing Philadelphia area">
      {# Leaflet map will be initialized here via JavaScript #}
      {# See docs/product/design/06-performance-strategy.md (Lines 525-585) #}
    </div>
    
    {# Map Controls #}
    <div class="map-controls" role="toolbar" aria-label="Map controls">
      <button 
        class="control-button" 
        aria-label="Zoom in"
        type="button"
        id="map-zoom-in"
      >
        <span class="icon-plus" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <button 
        class="control-button" 
        aria-label="Zoom out"
        type="button"
        id="map-zoom-out"
      >
        <span class="icon-minus" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <button 
        class="control-button" 
        aria-label="Center on current location"
        type="button"
        id="map-center-location"
      >
        <span class="icon-location" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
      <button 
        class="control-button" 
        aria-label="Toggle fullscreen"
        type="button"
        id="map-fullscreen"
      >
        <span class="icon-fullscreen" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </button>
    </div>
    
    {# Map Legend #}
    <div class="map-legend" role="complementary" aria-label="Map legend">
      <h4 class="legend-title">Risk Levels</h4>
      <ul class="legend-items">
        <li class="legend-item">
          <span class="legend-color" style="background: #22c55e;" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="legend-label">Low Risk (Z < 1.0)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="legend-item">
          <span class="legend-color" style="background: #eab308;" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="legend-label">Medium Risk (Z 1.0-2.0)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="legend-item">
          <span class="legend-color" style="background: #f97316;" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="legend-label">Elevated Risk (Z 2.0-3.0)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="legend-item">
          <span class="legend-color" style="background: #ef4444;" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="legend-label">High Risk (Z > 3.0)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    {# Loading State #}
    <div class="map-loading" aria-live="polite" aria-busy="true" role="status" hidden>
      <div class="loading-spinner" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <p>Loading crime data...</p>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  {# Alternative Data View (for screen readers and non-JS) #}
  <noscript>
    <div class="alternative-view">
      <h2>Crime Data</h2>
      <p>The interactive map requires JavaScript. You can view the data in table format:</p>
      <a href="/safety-map/data" class="button-primary">View Crime Data Table</a>
    </div>
  </noscript>
  
  {# Mobile Sidebar Toggle #}
  <button 
    class="sidebar-toggle" 
    aria-label="Toggle sidebar"
    aria-expanded="false"
    aria-controls="map-sidebar"
  >
    <span class="icon-menu" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  </button>
</div>

{# 
JavaScript Implementation Notes:

1. Initialize Leaflet Map:
   const map = L.map('crime-map').setView([39.9526, -75.1652], 12);
   L.tileLayer('https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png').addTo(map);

2. Add H3 Hexagon Layer:
   - Fetch hexagon data from API
   - Render polygons with color based on Z-score
   - Limit to 500 visible hexagons for performance
   - Cache hexagon boundaries

3. Add Marker Clustering:
   const markers = L.markerClusterGroup();
   // Add crime markers to cluster group

4. Implement Search:
   - Use geocoding API for address search
   - Center map on search result
   - Update risk summary for new location

5. Accessibility:
   - Announce map region changes to screen readers
   - Keyboard shortcuts for map controls
   - Focus management for modal dialogs

Reference:
- Performance: docs/product/design/06-performance-strategy.md (Lines 525-585)
- Accessibility: docs/product/design/05-accessibility-checklist.md (Lines 411-440)

Responsive Breakpoints:
- Mobile (< 768px): Sidebar hidden, toggle button shown
- Tablet (768px - 1023px): Sidebar 30%, map 70%
- Desktop (1024px+): Sidebar 25%, map 75%

See: docs/product/design/04-mobile-first-approach.md (Lines 63-140)
#}
